				\begin{document}$$\ge$$\end{document}≥ 10 ng/mL, and 90.2% had T1-T2 disease. 77 patients developed distal failure; 50 had perineural invasion (PNI). 7 patients developed local failure; 6/7 had PNI. The change in International Prostate Symptom Score (IPSS) after radiation treatment was 2.08 ± 6.19.
